.TH "TRANSFORMSTREAM.WRITABLE" "3JS" "November 26, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TransformStream.writable \- TransformStream: writable property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]writable\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]TransformStream\f[R] interface returns the
\f[CR]WritableStream\f[R] instance controlled by this
\f[CR]TransformStream\f[R].
This stream accepts input data that will be transformed and emitted to
the \f[CR]readable\f[R] stream.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]WritableStream\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
This example creates a \f[CR]TransformStream\f[R] that converts all
input text to uppercase letters.
It writes some text to the \f[CR]writable\f[R] stream, then reads the
transformed text from the \f[CR]readable\f[R] stream.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] stream = \f[B]new\f[R] TransformStream({
  transform(chunk, controller) {
    controller.enqueue(chunk.toUpperCase());
  },
});

\f[I]// Write data to be transformed\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] writer = stream.writable.getWriter();
writer.write(\(dqhello \(dq);
writer.write(\(dqworld\(dq);
writer.close();

\f[I]// Read transformed data\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] reader = stream.readable.getReader();
\f[B]let\f[R] done = \f[B]false\f[R];
\f[B]let\f[R] output = \(dq\(dq;
\f[B]while\f[R] (!done) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] result = \f[B]await\f[R] reader.read();
  \f[B]if\f[R] (result.value) {
    output += result.value;
  }
  done = result.done;
}
console.log(output); \f[I]// HELLO WORLD\f[R]
.EE
